      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "4495d56c5d136071",
        "text": "# Assess\n\n# What to do first\n\n* Assess the situation & orient yourself to the issue at hand.\n* Create response strategies, including what the triggers will be for a phase shift back to normal operation when the crisis is over.\n* Create your approach towards interventions and how to manage constraints.\n* Design Briefs, Goals and Missions, using material produced by the sensing networks.\n# Decisions to be made\n\n* If it isn't a crisis, then focus on Organisational resilience and monitor for outliers that indicate if the system is becoming over constrained.\n* If it is a crisis, decisions must be made quickly, authority and hierarchy is useful in these circumstances.\n* Set Draconian constraints, including to prevent premature convergence.\n* Capitalise on opportunities to make changes whilst the system is open to it.\n* Make focussed, tactical use of shallow dives into chaos, using small numbers from existing informal networks by relaxing constraints.\n# Tasks and activities\n\n* Create triggers to identify emerging issues which were unknowable beforehand.\n* Distribute the cognition\n* Create a map of the Dispositional Landscape\n* Start Journaling\n* Reset measures to the short-term, focus on the present, ahead of Crew design"
      },
